    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The freeze relates to consensus:\r\n\r\n1) **Deposit contract**: The [byte code](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/dev/deposit_contract/contracts/validator_registration.json) will not change. \r\n2) **State transition function**: `hash_tree_root(state_transition(state, block, true))` will not change for any input `state` and `block`.\r\n3) **Fork choice rule**: `get_head(store)`, `on_tick(store, time)`, `on_block(store, block)`, and `on_attestation(store, attestation)` will not change for any input `store`, `time`, `block`, and `attestation`.\r\n\r\nFor all the above, exceptions are made to critical bugs that prevent the formation of long-lived cross-client testnets. In addition to the above \"substantive freeze\" we abstain from disruptive cosmetic changes (e.g. significant renamings and refactors in `specs/core/0_beacon-chain.md`).\r\n\r\nSubstantive post-freeze changes will at minimum include:\r\n\r\n* Fixes to non-critical bugs found during the freeze\r\n* Change to BLS logic to comply with blockchain standards",
